'From Squeak3.7alpha of 11 September 2003 [latest update: #5764] on 11 March 2004 at 9:40:19 am'!"Change Set:		DependentsSizeFix-nkDate:			11 March 2004Author:			Ned KonzI noticed in the ChangeSorter that if you add a postscript, then close the editor window and try to remove the postscript that you can't.Further examination showed that there is code in postscriptHasDependents that says	self postscript dependents size > 0which returned true even though the dependents slots had been nil'd out.Though counting dependents is probably questionable, this change set makes DependentsArray>>size report the number of actual dependents (i.e. does not count nils)."!!DependentsArray methodsFor: 'copying' stamp: 'nk 3/11/2004 09:34'!size	^self inject: 0 into: [ :count :dep | dep ifNotNil: [ count _ count + 1 ]]! !!DependentsArray methodsFor: 'enumerating' stamp: 'nk 3/11/2004 09:34'!do: aBlock	"Refer to the comment in Collection|do:."	| dep |	1 to: self basicSize do:[:i|		(dep _ self at: i) ifNotNil:[aBlock value: dep]].! !